morning_landlady:
    clear_dialog
    set_stat day 3
    set_stat actions 6
    run transition_instant generic_wake
    set data.landlady.rentPrice 75

    stop music
    play music intro
    play sound doorknock
    "KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK."
    clear_dialog
    "There is a knocking at your front door. It's not a friendly knocking. The <span class='goldItalic'>golden light</span> is vaporised by the 'you are about to have to talk to someone at 9AM' adrenaline rush."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "*Another* knock at the door first thing in the morning? Someone's popular."
        "Oh me oh my! It's like the opening at Royal Ascot in this cottage lately!":
            talk lovely talk "Quite! Oh how I miss the races..."
        "Cor blimey it's like piccadilly bleedin circus ere!":
            talk nasty talk "Bloody is as well."
        "I have had two visitors over two days. That's a 100% visitation rate. I predict tomorrow I shall have a third."
            set data.ghost.predictedThirdVisitor true
            talk orb talk "An astute observation, Ghost. Let us observe how your hypothesis plays out tomorrow."
        "*More* visitors? I'm going to kill myself.":
            if (roll morning_landlady_kys_nightmare nightmare 20):
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>do it you fucking faggot.</span>"
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    if (!= (quest_succeeded? fixHouse) true):
        "A chill in the air. The hole in your ceiling shivers. You should really get that fixed before you catch your death of cold."
        clear_dialog
    play sound doorknock
    choice:
        "More knocking. Whoever is downstairs *really* wants to speak to you, and they *really* wish they didn't have to."
        "[Get dressed, and then go downstairs and open the front door]":
            if (!= (objective_started? houseSnake boneman) true):
                clear_dialog
                set_screen day_three
                play sound sting_day
                wait 8000
                set_screen generic_wake
            if $data.intro.smashedVase:
                run transition_study true
                wait 2000
                play sound punch
                run transition_study_pain
                choice:
                    "The moment you jump out of bed a pain shoots up your leg. You've stood on a shard of ceramic, specifically one of the shards *you* left on the floor when you intentionally smashed that vase the other day."
                    "\\"YOOOOOOOOOOOOOWL!\\" [Hop around on one foot while firmly grasping your injury]":
                        choice:
                            talk orb talk "Sorry Ghost but you're getting zero sympathy from me for this."
                            "[Grit your teeth and think this between tears] I'm fine! I'm fine! It's just a scratch! [Get dressed, and then go downstairs and open the front door]":
                                play sound footstepsinside
                                "Every step is agony, but you make it downstairs."
                                run transition_fromStudy intro_home
                                wait 2000
            clear_dialog
            play sound dooropen
            if (objective_started? houseSnake boneman):
                jump ending_boneman
            else:
                play music chilling
                run transition morning_landlady
                "Standing outside your door, is what can only be described as a 'votes tory' golem."
    clear_dialog
    start_quest landlady
    start_objective landlady rent
    choice:
        talk landlady talk "You were supposed to pay your rent two days ago, and yet here I stand with nary a penny to my name!"
        "\\"I never paid my rent?\\"":
            talk landlady talk "No! You certainly did not! In my day you'd be..."
        "\\"Okay. Why do I have to pay *you* rent exactly?\\"":
            choice:
                talk landlady talk "What do you mean, <span class='writtenText'>'why'</span>? Because this is *my* cottage, remember."
                "\\"I'm pretty sure it's mine actually.\\" [Point at the spare pair of boots on the doorstep] \\"Look, my boots.\\"":
                    set data.morning_landlady_boots true
                    "Your Landlady performatively rolls her eyes and scoffs."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk landlady talk "Are you unfamiliar with how renting works? You're a grown..."
        "[Shut the door]":
            play sound doorclose
            talk landlady talk "Gasp!"
            clear_dialog
            "She manages to poke a foot in the door, stopping you from closing it."
            clear_dialog
            talk landlady talk "The nerve of you! In my day you'd be..."
    clear_dialog
    "Your Landlady trails off. Something has caught her eye. Her mouth falls agape. Some of her hairs stand on end. A pearl pops off of her necklace."
    clear_dialog
    if (!= $data.ghost.roofRepaired true):
        set data.landlady.sawRoof true
        choice:
            talk landlady talk "I- is that a *hole* in my roof!?"
            "\\"Yes.\\"":
                "Your Landlady draws a crown across her chest (a quite complicated movement) and mutters something."
            "\\"No.\\" [Lie]":
                "Your Landlady rubs her eyes and double checks your roof. It's still got a hole in it. She draws a crown across her chest (a quite complicated movement) and mutters something."
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>appalling. you still haven't repaired your roof. what are you, an animal?</span>"
            "I am literally a smelly rat.":
                choice:
                    talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>most rats are very clean. you're just a disgusting fucking basement dweller.</span>"
                    "It's more of an attic, actually.":
                        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>shut the fuck up. kill yourself.</span>"
            "Orb am I an animal?":
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "What?"
                    "I asked if I am an animal.":
                        talk orb talk "Uh, yes? I suppose so?"
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk landlady talk "*What* have you *done* to *my* cottage!?"
            "\\"In my defence, I didn't do it. Orb did.\\"":
                "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
            "\\"I'm constricting a new chimney for you.\\" [Nod reassuringly]":
                choice:
                    talk landlady talk "You're... you're <span class='writtenText'>'constricting a new chimney'</span> for me? T- that- I don't *want* a new chimney! Dawnsight give me strength... what *are* you playing at!?"
                    "I can throw in some spice racks too, if you don't mind me knocking down some of the load bearing walls. [Do a gay little sledgehammer motion at your doorway]":
                        "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
                    "Sorry, I was joking. I'm not really constricting a new chimney for you.":
                        talk landlady talk "T- then why did you..."
                        clear_dialog
                        "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
            "[Point at your spare pair of boots again] \\"Boots.\\"" if $data.morning_landlady_boots:
                "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
    else:
        choice:
            talk landlady talk "D- did you break my roof and then repair it by nailing a single plank to the ceiling?"
            "[Nod proudly] \\"You're looking at a dyke, mam, you *bet* I did that.\\"" if (!= $data.raven.fixedRoof true):
                "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
            "\\"Heh. No. I outsourced it to a dyke.\\" [Tap your head] \\"Work smarter not harder.\\"" if $data.raven.fixedRoof:
                "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
            "\\"It was like that when I got here.\\" [Lie]":
                talk landlady talk "It most certainly was not!"
                clear_dialog
                "Your Landlady looks like she wants to cry. Good job!"
    if $data.intro.smashedVase:
        clear_dialog
        "Your Landlady takes yet another psychic hit. She has made the grave error of looking down."
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk landlady talk "I- is that *blood* flooding out of your boot!?"
            "[Look down]":
                choice:
                    "Yup. It's blood. The ceramic shard appears to have cut you pretty badly. Your boot is overflowing with blood."
                    "[Look back up at Your Landlady] \\"Looks like it yes!\\" [Nod]":
                        "Your Landlady looks faint. Even more so than you, somehow, despite her not being the one losing several pints of blood."
                        clear_dialog
                        play sound punch
                        choice:
                            "For a brief moment worker and parasite are one. Your Landlady faints."
                            "[Faint]":
                                pause music
                                play sound punch
                                clear_dialog
                                run transition_instant generic_black
                                animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                                wait 8000
                                resume music
                                choice:
                                    "It is you who wakes up first. Your wound seems to have clotted, you're alive."
                                    "[Stand back up]":
                                        talk lovely talk "Oh me oh my! Are you okay, darling? That was quite horrible!"
                                        talk nasty talk "Just a fucking scratch innit. I'll kiss it better if you want."
                                        talk orb talk "Do *not* let Nasty Girl kiss it better. I *know* where her mouth has been."
                                        talk nasty talk "EHEHEHAHAHA!"
                                        run transition morning_landlady
                                        clear_dialog
                                        "You miraculously feel fine now, and stand up just in time to see your Landlady also recover. She clambers to her feet. The most manual labour she has done in a long time."
                                        if (roll morning_landlady_trick_nasty nasty 20):
                                            set data.landlady.nastyTrick true
                                            talk nasty talk "Quick. Here's your chance. Just tell her you paid the fucking rent and tell her to piss off."
                                        else:
                                            wait 1000
                                        clear_dialog
                                        choice:
                                            talk landlady talk "Good heavens, w- was I asleep?"
                                            "\\"You were. You were collecting my rent, which I paid in full by the way, and it made you so tired that you needed a nap and then you went to sleep on the doorstep.\\"" if $data.landlady.nastyTrick:
                                                "Your Landlady looks a little bemused. That doesn't *sound* like something she would do..."
                                                if (roll morning_landlady_lightheaded_lovely lovely 20):
                                                    talk lovely talk "Usually she'd never take a tenants word as fact, but she's feeling awfully light-headed."
                                                else:
                                                    wait 1000
                                                clear_dialog
                                                talk landlady talk "As you say. Yes. Rent paid..."
                                                clear_dialog
                                                "She sways, slightly."
                                                clear_dialog
                                                talk landlady talk "Well, thank you for your prompt payment. I'll see you next month, yes?"
                                                clear_dialog
                                                complete_quest landlady landladyNegotiateSuccess
                                                unlock_achievement gaslight
                                                run transition generic_door
                                                "Your Landlady wanders down the lane to her automobile."
                                                play sound caraway
                                                "There is a horrible clattering and roaring as Your Landlady's automobile starts up."
                                                play sound baa
                                                "A nearby sheep bleats angrily in response."
                                                clear_dialog
                                                choice:
                                                    talk orb talk "Wonderful, having expertly sidestepped this tedious plot line we can get back to whatever you had planned for today."
                                                    "\\"Wandering about, mostly.\\" [Go outside]":
                                                        jump morning_landlady_end
                                            "\\"You were. I guess the excitement of collecting my rent got too much for you and you fell asleep. I still need to pay my rent, by the way. I'm a loyal tenant.\\"":
                                                if $data.landlady.nastyTrick:
                                                    talk nasty talk "Cuuuuuuck. Fucking brain cuck."
                                                    clear_dialog
                                                "Your Landlady looks a little bemused. That doesn't *sound* like something she would do... a landlady would no sooner fall asleep mere meters from her rent money than a predator would mere meters from its prey..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk landlady talk "Look. I have to take Timothy, Tomothy, Matilda and Marthtilda to their violin lessons, and so I do *not* have time for this nonsense. I have a busy life outside of slaving away for my tenants, you know?"
        "\\"Seems it.\\"":
            run skip
        "\\"Violin? Congrats on your homosexual children Mam!\\"":
            talk landlady talk "The word you're looking for is <span class='writtenText'>'cultured'</span>. They are my well mannered, well educated, cultured little gems."
            if (roll morning_landlady_tomothy_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "Tomothy's main hobby is setting bugs on fire with a magnifying glass."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "Your Landlady's face sinks into a sort of low-level ambient scowl."
    if (roll morning_landlady_scowl_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "She's not used to having to bicker this much before she's handed a wad of cash."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    if $data.ghost.roofRepaired:
        talk landlady talk "Bring me seventy-five pounds by tomorrow night, or I'm phoning the neighbourhood watch, the council and the local constable and having you thrown out."
        talk landlady talk "My address is written on the contract you signed when you moved in. The contract that *explicitly* stated you were responsible for paying rent."
    else:
        add data.landlady.rentPrice 25
        talk landlady talk "Bring me one hundred pounds by tomorrow night, or I'm phoning the neighbourhood watch, the council and the local constable and having you thrown out."
        talk landlady talk "*Usually* I'd charge less, but *usually* my lovely tiled roof isn't..."
        clear_dialog
        "She sighs."
        if (roll morning_landlady_friend_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "The friend of her husband she usually contracts for repairs is on holiday, and she's worried the damp will have set in by then. No she will not hire a more expensive, actually qualified contractor to get it fixed faster."
            talk nasty talk "Blessed life. Godspeed, husbands' friend who does repairs."
        else:
            wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        talk landlady talk "My address is written on the contract you signed when you moved in. The contract that *explicitly* stated you were responsible for paying rent and *not* damaging the building."
    clear_dialog
    if (>= $stats.money.value $data.landlady.rentPrice):
        set data.landlady.rentPriceText (numbverter $data.landlady.rentPrice)
        choice:
            talk landlady talk "You'll have to pop over during the evening because I'm *busy* during the day."
            "[Leave your rent unpaid for now]":
                run skip
            "[In a booming voice, somehow without opening your mouth] \\"I need not this pitiful rendezvous, woman. I can pay you now.\\" [Thrust %{$data.landlady.rentPriceText} pounds into her paws]":
                "Your Landlady is knocked back by the force of your speech."
                clear_dialog
                talk landlady talk "S- such power!"
                clear_dialog
                if (== $data.landlady.rentPrice 100):
                    add_stat money -100
                if (== $data.landlady.rentPrice 80):
                    add_stat money -80
                if (== $data.landlady.rentPrice 75):
                    add_stat money -75
                if (== $data.landlady.rentPrice 55):
                    add_stat money -55
                play sound coins
                "Your Landlady counts through the money. It passes through her hands like cards in a casinos' shuffler. Water through a river. A cruel woman's fingers down another woman's salivating throat."
                "Your Landlady likes how the pennies and notes feel against her fingers. Cold. Hard. Soft. Each unique. Each now *hers*."
                "It takes her less than two seconds to count. She's had practise. She counts it two more times anyway."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk landlady talk "Wonderful. I'll see you in a month Ms..."
                    "\\"It's Ghost.\\"":
                        talk landlady talk "Hmm. Yes, Ms Ghost."
                        if (roll landlady_pay_name_lovely lovely 20):
                            talk lovely talk "She genuinely couldn't recall your name."
                        else:
                            wait 1000
                clear_dialog
                talk landlady talk "Ta ta now. Cheerio."
                complete_objective landlady rent
                complete_quest landlady landladySuccess
                unlock_achievement rent
    else:
        talk landlady talk "You'll have to pop over during the evening because I'm *busy* during the day."
        if (roll morning_landlady_busy_orb orb 20):
            talk orb talk "She's busy, but she isn't working. Day drinking, curtain twitching and writing letters to mumsnest, mostly."
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    run transition generic_door
    "With that, your Landlady wanders down the lane to her automobile, muttering to herself the whole way."
    clear_dialog
    if (roll morning_landlady_complaing_orb orb 40):
        set data.global.orbMonoxideLeak true
        choice:
            talk orb talk "She's complaining about how her hard work maintaining the cottage is never appreciated."
            "Has she worked hard to maintain it?":
                talk orb talk "No. There's some damp hidden behind a wardrobe, a colony of frogs under the kitchen floorboards... oh, and there's a gas leak, so your ambient carbon monoxide levels are... well, you'll live. If you think you're being bitten by ants, don't worry, they're not real."
                clear_dialog
    play sound caraway 3
    "There is a horrible clattering and roaring as Your Landlady's automobile starts up. A nearby sheep bleats angrily in response."
    clear_dialog
    if (!= (quest_succeeded? landlady) true):
        choice:
            talk orb talk "We should check out that contract she mentioned, it's on your kitchen table, you messy messy woman."
            "[Head inside and look at your contract]":
                clear_dialog
                "You find the contract where Orb said it would be. It's long. Too long to bother reading, but you're able to find Your Landlady's address. <span class='writtenText'>'12 Lamprey Lane, Little Donking'</span>."
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "Well, at least now we know where she lives. We should probably make sure we pay your rent, or you're going to be living in the field with the sheep, and something tells me The Weapon won't best be pleased with that."
                    "[Go outside]":
                        jump morning_landlady_end
    else:
        jump morning_landlady_end

morning_landlady_end:
    clear_dialog
    "Autumn has shifted another gear into winter. It's a chilly, grim day."
    choice:
        "A cold breeze brushes your cheek like a lovers caress. Or snowman's caress. Or both, if you're into that. Whatever your preference, it's time to start the day."
        "Good morning world! [Do a gay little wave at the world] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            "The world does not wave back."
            jump goToGameMap
        "I'd probably bang a snowman if I had the chance. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            talk orb talk "Excuse me?"
            talk nasty talk "Don't. Doesn't end well, believe you me."
            jump goToGameMap